==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intensify
<hw>In*ten"si*fy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Intensified</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Intensifying</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[<ets>Intense</ets> + <ets>-fly</ets>.]</ety> <def>To render more
intense; <as>as, to <ex>intensify</ex> heat or cold; to
<ex>intensify</ex> colors; to <ex>intensify</ex> a photographic
negative; to <ex>intensify</ex> animosity.</as></def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How piercing is the sting of pride⟦br⟧
By want embittered and <qex>intensified</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intensify</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Intensify
<hw>In*ten"si*fy</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become intense, or more
intense; to act with increasing power or energy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>intensifying</ent>⟦br⟧
